==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Redemptionist
<hw>Re*demp"tion*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(R.C.Ch.)</fld> <def>A
monk of an order founded in 1197; -- so called because the order was
especially devoted to the redemption of Christians held in captivity by
the Mohammedans. Called also <altname>Trinitarian</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Redemptive</ent>⟦br⟧
